Package: saguiSED
Title: Optional SED-Fitting Backends for SAGUI Regional Photometry
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Rafael", "S. de Souza",
           email = "rd23aag@herts.ac.uk",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides optional SED-fitting helpers for SAGUI regional
    photometry. The package keeps heavy Python SED-fitting dependencies outside
    the core sagui package while exposing a compact R interface for fitting
    segmented regions and painting physical-property summaries back onto the
    image plane.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Depends:
    R (>= 4.1.0)
Imports:
    ggplot2,
    jsonlite,
    stats,
    utils
Suggests:
    FITSio,
    sagui,
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
